lender.name: Lassine S
lender.occupational_info:
Our Current Micro Projects in Koungojan MALI
In addition to our health and education programs, in 2004 we started our first Micro Program, helping the village women association by purchasing and installing a Moulin. The Moulin grinds maize, millet, rice and karite nuts among others, and has reduced the manual work by 70%. The women association manages the Moulin in Koungojan, facilitating the work of the women. Thanks to the Moulin, the women have time to cultivate a vegetable garden and sell their harvest at the market.
The profits are place in the community savings account of the village, and in turn, it can lend small sums to the villagers. - thanks to DIHS who installed the Moulin, life of the village women has changed, the work is less painful (better tools, machines...) One produces more, one sells more, the money circulates more and the standard of living increases. DIHS is trying to implement the Revalorization of the Women, the elimination of illiteracy, and the formation and management by the villagers themselves. The village begins to see reduced urban migration (towards Bamako or other African countries).
